episode_name: Pod. 181 Rekti Yoewono TALKS ABOUT BEING KNOWN FOR THE WRONG REASON
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Rekti Yoewono talks about making underground music, not looking for success, and an NFT drop.  Who doesn’t know Rekti Yoewono, a musician from Bandung, vocalist of The SIGIT, and bassist from a stoner-rock band called Mooner. Aside from producing new and fresh bands, he is a record collector who recently got himself into the world of NFT. He believes in doing what you can as much as you can, but still, you need to take it easy on yourself, and throughout his life, the only person he can expect something from is none other than himself. Listen to his story only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 180 Dendy Darman TALKS ABOUT 25 YEARS OF A SMALL BUSINESS
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Dendy Darman talks about swell riding, keeping it casual, and raising a jenglot.  In Bandung, 1996, a local brand called unkl347 was born and has become a pioneer in the local fashion industry until now. Dendy Darman, the founder of unkl347, is a designer who knows no limits to creativity. He runs his business naturally by just letting it flow and being flexible. Get clued up about his journey, where he believes there is no standard or a certain way to run a business. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 179 TALKS ABOUT A CELEBRATION OF CINEMA WITH INDONESIAN FILMMAKERS
description: A discussion with Indonesia’s top filmmakers about progress, achievements and what it takes to create the ideal film industry we all wished for.  In today’s episode of Makna Talks, along with @netflix.id, we spotlight the anatomy of the country’s film industry based on the facts and the behaviors of film enthusiasts in Indonesia. Together with Shanty Harmayn, Muhammad Zaidy, Ernest Prakasa, and Mira Lesmana, they shared their point of view and their thoughts on how challenges lay ahead. Yet, there is much promising progress to mark the film industry’s recovery. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 178 Arawinda TALKS ABOUT THE FIRST ROLE
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Arawinda talks about finding discipline through dancing, a debut on the screen, and leaving to come back.  Arawinda managed to make herself known by the public by winning Festival Indonesia (FFI) award for the Best Female Leading Actor category through her debut in Yuni. Ever since then, the career of this 20-year-old talented young woman has been rising up. Although she’s still young, she’s able to become an inspirational figure through her arts. Apart from acting, she also pursues her career in the industry through dancing and singing. Listen to her story now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 177 Muhammad Sadad TALKS ABOUT MAKING MILLIONS OVERNIGHT
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Muhammad Sadad talks about chin being high at the wrong time, a fashion week, and the beginning of a new chapter.  Experience is the best teacher, and failure is a part of the process. The same thing happened to Muhammad Sadad, founder of Erigo. Despite having to endure a roller coaster ride, he successfully made a profit of up to billions from his business. Sadad believes hard times will lead you to something great because achieving your dreams doesn’t come instantly. Listen to his long journey to success only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 176 Andi Taufan TALKS ABOUT INVESTING IN WOMAN
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Andi Taufan talks about solving close-to-home problems, a change of plan, and what Rp.100,000 can do.   Andi Taufan Garuda Putra, the founder of a peer-to-peer lending company, Amartha, has been impacting many women in the countryside who are interested in opening a business by providing initial capital of up to Rp10 million to empower them in building their businesses. Until today Amartha have been funded more than 1 million women micro entrepreneurs!  Andi Taufan has been to many places, from 9-5 jobs to the government and continuing with what he started with Amartha. Listen to his journey now, only on Spotify! - Rp100.000 might be a small amount of money for some of us. But for others, it meant a million opportunities.  Be a funder and use the code ANDI100 worth Rp100.000 funding bonus for the first 250 listeners of this episode! For more information on this campaign, listen to the episode or visit www.amartha.com & @amarthaid. #100RibuSejutaPeluang

episode_name: Pod. 175 Daniel Mananta TALKS ABOUT WHEN NOTHING GOES RIGHT
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Daniel Mananta talks about a sad young boy being compared at all times and having faith.  The first thing that comes to mind when people think about Daniel Mananta is the word presenter. Because of his consistency in the industry, he’s able to gain people's trust and meet their expectations because he’s capable of meetings everyone’s expectations by always giving the same level of quality and commitment that speaks from his works. He keeps on fascinating people with his perspective about life and communicating it with others. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 174 Lukman Sardi TALKS ABOUT GETTING IN AND OUT OF CHARACTERS
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Lukman Sardi talks about a traumatizing childhood, waking up at five, and a safe space for women.  Known in the world of acting as a top actor and often stars in several big-screen movies, Lukman Sardi started to get noticed by people for his talent because of his professional acting and the characters he’s been playing. As a result, he managed to receive awards and gain popularity from it. In this chance, Lukman Sardi opens up about his days before being well known, the world of acting, and some things happening under the table. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 173 Darwis Triadi TALKS ABOUT BEYOND PHOTOGRAPHY
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Darwis Triadi talks about characters that shape mankind, a promise to keep, and a presidential visit.  Darwis Triadi’s decades of experience in the world of photography have made him highly respected, and it’s safe to say he has become a photography icon in Indonesia. Even though photography wasn’t his first career option, he became one of the most well-known figures in the industry by being consistent and bringing out top-notch works. He shares his four-decade journey, some unforgettable experiences, and legendary stories in this episode. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 172 Dr. Asmin Fransiska TALKS ABOUT THE HUMAN RIGHTS BEHIND BARS
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Dr. Asmin Fransiska talks about the Indonesian narcotics law, overcapacity of prisons, and ways we can help.  #BayangkanJikaKamu terkena kasus narkoba dan diperlakukan secara tidak adil secara hukum, apa yang akan kamu lakukan?   Last week we had the chance to talk with Nandha, a former drug convict. And on this episode, we had the opportunity to sit down with Dr. Asmin Fransiska, a drug law expert, where she explains the real problems behind bars from her perspective. On top of that, Dr. Asmin unravels the country’s law system and how it affects the occurrences, also what we, the society can do to change the situation. Listen now, only on  Spotify!  If you’re done listening, support our friends from @aksikeadilan @lbhmasyarakat @kontras_udpate @ijrs_official @icjrid @lovefrankieco and sign the petition to help fix this issue on change.org/reformasipenjara. #NapiJugaManusia

episode_name: Pod. 171 Nandha TALKS ABOUT 9 YEARS BEHIND BARS FOR SOMEONE ELSE’S CRIME
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Nandha talks about the ugly truth of prisons, being heartless and second chances.  #BayangkanJikaKamu menjalani masa pandemi dalam satu ruangan kecil dengan 30 orang, sulit mendapat akses kesehatan, harus bertahan selama bertahun-tahun, apa yang akan kamu rasakan?  In this episode, we had the opportunity to sit down with Nandha, a former drug convict, to tell her reality behind bars. She shared with us how she became convicted of something she didn’t do, the overcrowded cells, and the treatments that are far from just. The overcrowding issue is caused mainly by the high rates of drug-related convictions. It caused numerous problems ranging from cramped space, poor sanitation, poor air circulation, and a lack of nutritious food intake, leading to riots. We can only imagine how it adds up with the pandemic we’re facing.   Listen to her story on our Spotify.  If you’re done listening, support our friends from @aksikeadilan @lbhmasyarakat @kontras_udpate @ijrs_official @icjrid @lovefrankieco and sign the petition to help fix this issue on change.org/reformasipenjara. #NapiJugaManusia

episode_name: Pod. 170 Tri Wardoyo TALKS ABOUT THE IMMORTALITY OF TWO SOULS
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Tri Wardoyo talks about the 5 stages of grief, meeting his childhood trauma, and acceptance.  In a career spanning from years to years in the music and event industry, Tri Wardoyo has developed deep links and constantly inspires others. With things changing radically in his world, he tries to make adjustments, grow, and heal. On this opportunity, let's learn how he deals with his grief, what has helped him, and ways he honor and keep connections with the memories of his spouse. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 169 Kamengski TALKS ABOUT THE FINE LINE OF PLAGIARISM
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Kamengski talks about early 2000, a twist of design and no annual plans.  Just like their tag line, “In fun, we trust,” Kamengski succeeds in bringing up funny parody products that the market enjoys. Founder and creative director of Kamengski, Sulaiman Said, believes there are many exciting things from our everyday life that can be implemented into visual products. Loosen up and take notice of the journey behind Kamengski’s successful story, from parody to good business. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 168 Kiki Aulia Ucup TALKS ABOUT FAREWELL FOR NOW
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Kiki Aulia Ucup talks about leaving Synchronize Fest, the most famous individual on the phone, and bringing a weapon to school.  Kiki Aulia Ucup is an Indonesian music industry activist. He is best known as a talents manager, music festival program director, and event host. Because of his notable positioning in the industry, he became an important figure in the country’s music industry. Pin your ears back, and hear Ucup’s story on how he can be where he’s at right now. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 167 Dikta and Mario Zwinkle TALKS ABOUT TWO GREAT OPTIONS
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Dikta and Mario Zwinkle talks about growing up different and accomplishments #PickYourOptions  Pradikta Wicaksono, known as Dikta, is a musician and actor that has been in the industry for quite some time. He focuses on bringing fresh pop and blues tunes. Whereas Mario Zwinkle, a musician who started his career in 2012, traveled from his hometown to bring his colors to hip-hop. Throughout their journey, they manage their time with hobbies while overcoming challenges to be the very best in the music industry. What’s more, they shared their stories on dealing with great choices in their life. How do they do it? Tune in to this conversation, and at the same time, let’s pick your options. Listen now, only on Spotify!  #PickYourOptions #LetsTalkAboutYourOptions

episode_name: Talks Live at Synchronize Fest Di Radio: Workshop Kehidupan with Oomleo
description: Talks Live at Synchronize Fest Di Radio: Workshop Kehidupan with Oomleo  Last Monday at the Synchronize Fest Di Radio, we had the opportunity to sit down and talk with Oomleo. Join the conversation, along with our host, Iyas Lawrence, to discuss about “Workshop Kehidupan”. Listen now on Spotify!  #MaknaTalks™️ #SynchronizeFest #SynchronizeRadio

episode_name: Pod. 166 Christine Hakim TALKS ABOUT 50 YEARS IN THE INDUSTRY
description: Pod. 166 Christine Hakim TALKS ABOUT 50 YEARS IN THE INDUSTRY  In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Christine Hakim talks about understanding God on a war-ship, in the zone for roles, and stopping when told.  Indonesian film enthusiasts must be very familiar with Christine Hakim, a senior actress that has colored the film industry since the 70s. Since then, safe to say she has been one of the most influential people in the field. Throughout her career, she has won many awards. And not only working as an actress, her love for the world of cinema made her plunge into being a movie observer and producer. This time, go deep into her long unstoppable journey in the industry, including her intriguing work at Seperti Dendam, Rindu Harus Dibayar Tuntas. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 165 Audrey Tapiheru TALKS ABOUT BRINGING BACK THE RETRO VIBE
description: In today’s episode Makna Talks, Audrey Tapiheru talks about a loss of a father, being pushed to make music, and brighter colors to recover.  As a member of the pop trio group GAC, Audrey Tapiheru has gathered a decade of experience in the music industry. Not to mention all the awards that have been received throughout her journey along with the group. Furthermore, after two years of long hiatus, she decided to get back up into the game by releasing a solo EP, after the loss of her father. In this episode, she spilled all stories out for you to hear. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 164 Dira Sugandi TALKS ABOUT BEING HAPPY WITH ORDINARY
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Dira Sugandi talks about 95% theory, apologizing first, and putting happiness first.  Dira Sugandi is no stranger to the Indonesian music scene. She began to be widely known by the public when she performed with Incognito. Since then, Dira has continued to rise with her extraordinary talent & collaborated with international artists. Music has been there forever in her life, and we can say it is meant to be. Join into our conversation with Dira Sugandi and dig more behind her music together! Listen now, only on Spotify.

episode_name: Pod. 163 Jaz Hayat TALKS ABOUT RUINING AN APOLOGY WITH AN EXCUSE
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Jaz Hayat talks about home, saying goodbye to the one he loves most and meeting his mother for the first time.  Bruneian singer Jaz Hayat made his music debut in 2016 with a song called Dari Matamu. He appears to attract Indonesian music enthusiasts, and as a result of his hard work in the industry, he received several music awards. He never thought that music would be his choice of life, that he could make a living out of it. Having lived here long enough, Jaz has known Indonesia pretty well, including its people. Nonetheless, leaving home is never easy. Listen now, only on Spotify! Get cozy, and let’s dive into his heartfelt journey.

episode_name: Pod. 162 Mezzaluna TALKS ABOUT HAVING A NOT-SO-ROCKSTAR FATHER
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Mezzaluna talks about music during the pandemic, not liking the spotlight, and a father like no other. Mezzaluna made her debut as a solo singer recently with her single, In Situ, which tells a story of despair. Growing up with a legendary father, Bimbim from Slank, who is well known in the music industry, he immediately became her role model in music. However, Mezzaluna is not all in for the spotlight. She offers a distinctive style in her works while trying to keep her true sense of self. Keep your ears open and hear her story of making music, trying to live a typical teenage life, and of course, her living legend father. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 161 Raisa Andriana TALKS ABOUT DARING TO DREAM AND MAKING IT HAPPEN
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Raisa talks about being doubted, self confidence, and achieving dreams through consistency After more than a year, we met again virtually with Raisa to talk about her life since we spoke in Season 2. In this episode, we collaborated with Sunsilk and talked more about her dreams, the untold story behind her journey in achieving her journey to achieve her long-cherished dream, how she overcome each struggle, and what’s next on Raisa’s list. Listen to the full version on Spotify! Not only Raisa, you can make your dreams come true too! Starting from here, dare yourself to achieve your dreams. Write down your dreams at sunsilk.co.id/tak-terhentikan-tuk-berkilau and get a variety of FREE self-development classes to hone your potential. Starting from soft skills classes such as how to plan a dream, recognize your potential, communicate skills and get certificate, to a Rp100,000 discount voucher for access to any class at Skill Academy. Because your dream is too good to hold back. With Sunsilk, be #TakTerhentikanTukBerkilau!

episode_name: Pod. 160 Nia Dinata TALKS ABOUT DOUBLE TAPPING THE CRITICS
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Nia Dinata talks about life in nine years, normalizing minorities, and ways to not give a fuck.    Nia Dinata started her career directing music video clips and advertising. In early 2000, Nia expanded her creativity and created her own independent film company. From that day on, she’s known as the director and producer of numerous notable and influential movies—which received many awards and appreciation. In this opportunity, Nia shared her adventures beyond the screen. Listen now only on Spotify!

episode_name: POD. 159 Jerome Kurnia TALKS ABOUT PLAYING ROLES FOR LIFE
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Jerome Kurnia talks about calling a best friend, the story of saying goodbye but not leaving, and being the next big thing.  Indonesian actor, Jerome Kurnia, is not a newbie in his field because of his experiences in theater groups and art competitions since he was a child. Jerome is known for his role in The Earth of Mankind and many other top movies and TV series. While enjoying the fruit of his hard work, he has become a whole new person with a new set of vision and mission in acting while still managing to get in several roles for big-screen movies. Get a load of what his acting journey looks like and how he appreciates every little thing in life.   Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: POD. 158 Teza Sumendra TALKS ABOUT MAKING FRIENDS IN THE INDUSTRY
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Teza Sumendra talks about being present every night, sensual tunes, and surviving by socializing.  If you were to ask who’s the best R&B singer in Indonesia amongst the millennial generation, it's safe to say that Teza Sumendra is on the list. He delivers a different level of melodies, rhythms, funk grooves, combining it with his famous deep, charismatic voice that emphasizes the soulful elements of his music. In this opportunity, we get into an in-depth conversation with Teza about his works, how he shows up for people, and how he keeps his body and soul together. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: POD. 157 Jessica Bunga TALKS ABOUT A RED CARPET WELCOME IN THE INDUSTRY
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Jessica Bunga talks about making a tough decision, being 20 and stop giving out advices.  For all Gen Z TikTok users out there, the name Jessica Bunga or better known as Jebung is certainly not strange to the ears. She is acclaimed for her golden voice and her humorous personality, that can be seen in all of her videos. Who would’ve thought that we could finally hear her story on her sudden outbreak? This time, Jebung tells her story on her journey as a singer and also a content creator. Tune in as we reveal her reaction for her very first viral video on TikTok! Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod.156 Iwet Ramadhan TALKS ABOUT STORIES OF EACH STROKES THAT CREATES EMOTIONAL PATTERNS
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Iwet Ramadhan talks about 19 years on air, being a face member, and preserving a fabric.  Who doesn't know this Indonesian radio broadcaster that has been on the air for almost two decades? But other than that, Iwet Ramadhan is also known as an extraordinary entrepreneur and a passionate cultural enthusiast. His love for culture is expressed in all his business ventures where he introduces and preserves Batik. Tune in to this conversation, and learn about his voyage in becoming a Batik enthusiast. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 155 Adit Insomnia TALKS ABOUT NO PLANS AHEAD
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Adit Insomnia talks about life in the dark, a different kind of happiness and a priceless gift.  Adit Insomnia, a renowned Radio Broadcaster, host, and a friend of us from our audio drama series, Kelas Puber. Adit is here to join us for a good time as we discuss random topics, his days full of laughter, and a deeper point of view that we rarely see from him. Be all ears and enjoy this conversation, where Iyas & Adit laugh their time away on this episode. Also, are you ready to hear Adit’s surprising announcement? We know we are! Listen now only on Spotify.

episode_name: Pod. 154 Axton Salim TALKS ABOUT REDEFINING YOUR SUCCESS AND FAILURES
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Axton Salim talks about directing a worldwide company, keeping the shelves filled, and pressures of growing adults. Axton Salim is a renowned businessman in Indonesia. Carrying his title as Indofood’s Director and CMO since 2009, also his viral posts on social media, his name indeed is not a stranger to the ears. Through his achievements certainly shows how he is the right person for the job. But in this episode, we’ll get to see everything behind the success through his lens. Join us as Axton Salim explain the journey through the ups and downs and everything in between. Sit back, relax, and enjoy the episode!

episode_name: Pod. 153 Sean Gelael TALKS ABOUT BEING IN CONTROL OF HIS OWN TRACK
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Sean Gelael talks about being on a podium, an Ibiza training camp and a tribute to Anthoine.  Indonesian racer, Sean Gelael has been familiar with the racing world since he was only 9 years old. At a very young age, Sean had the courage to take part in the Sprint Rally national championship by becoming a navigator for his own father. Since then, he has won many championships and his career has continued to excell. His latest accomplishment was setting a record as the first Indonesian racer to climb the podium at Le Mans 2021. In his long racing journey, there has been many unforgettable moments, as well as how it all pays off for Sean. Buckle up and be all ears to this interesting story of him. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 152 Faye Simanjuntak TALKS ABOUT MAKING CHANGE ONE CHILD AT A TIME
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Faye Simanjuntak talks about making good use of privilege, bias stories on the dinner table and the mastermind at home.  Others often misjudge Faye Simanjuntak because of her young age. But, that doesn’t stop her from doing what she’s passionate about and the things that she wants to pursue. As the founder of Rumah Faye, she focuses on freeing Indonesian children from child trafficking, violence, and exploitation. Her expertise includes many aspects such as sexual and reproductive health and rights, gender-based violence, also youth participation, and leadership. With the privilege given by her family, she knows how to take good advantage of it and make it beneficial for others. This minute, we plunge into her long journey. Listen now only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 151 Teguh Surya & Uslaini Chaus TALKS ABOUT THE INCOMING DISASTER
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Teguh Surya & Uslaini Chaus talks about funds from Europe, facts of deforestations, and having 9 years left.  Uslaini Chaus, Director of WALHI, an Indonesian based environmental NGO in West Sumatera, has been speaking out about being cautious of environmental problems in Indonesia. Alongside Teguh Surya, for Yayasan Madani Berkelanjutan, they both fight for the preservation of the environment, and raising awareness to help Indonesians live a better, healthier life. Did you know that we only have 9 years left to help the environment before it’s too late? Did you know that the acts of deforestation are getting worse and worse by day? What can we do to help the environment and saving ourselves? We’ll help answer through this very insightful episode. It’s never too late to start. Sit back and enjoy! Listen now only on Spotify.

episode_name: Pod. 150 Alissa Wahid TALKS ABOUT THE DISAPPEARANCE OF TOLERANCE AND ITS PSYCHOLOGICAL IMPACTS
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Alissa Wahid talks about equal rights for all, pleasing the bullies and stories of Gus Dur.  Alissa Wahid, a psychologist, humanitarian, activist, and the national director of Gusdurian Network Indonesia, actively manages a social project which focuses on the self-development of children and reproductive health. Aside from pursuing her main career and social activities she is also working on various diverse organizations. To open up Season 4, in collaboration with @CerdasBerkarakter.KemdikbudRI and @Kemdikbud.RI, @Alissa_Wahid shared her insights on unpacking diverse understanding of intolerance, the psychological impacts of intolerance, renewing the spirit of freedom and independence, as well as how bullying is a big problem with big consequences. Moreover, she talked about continuing her family’s legacy, what living at the national palace feels like, and all of her best memoirs of Gus Dur.  Listen to the full conversation on Spotify, or you can also watch the short version on Youtube!  This episode was recorded at Home, from Jakarta and Yogyakarta. Enjoy our long distance conversation!

episode_name: Pod. 149 Ed Sheeran TALKS ABOUT REMEMBERING HOW IT FEELS TO FALL FOR MUSIC
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Ed Sheeran talks about a depressing song, speaking Italian and Ed’s Bad Habit. Who does not know the English musician Ed Sheeran in this existence? Everybody knows him. He is not just an ordinary solo singer. Apart from being a songwriter, guitarist, and record producer, he was named one of the best-selling music artists in the world. All the hard work, sacrifices, struggles, and downfalls faced by Ed paid off, and now he is on top of his successful career. In this final episode of Season 3, we have the opportunity to hear about his personal stories, from his morning routines, all the things he does during the pandemic, to finding a new hobby that's still creative but no one can see nor judge. Furthermore, he is also sharing how being a father is the best chapter of his life and, of course, about his new music, where he is starting up again and having the same excitement he had ten years ago. Listen now only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 148 Iqbaal Ramadhan TALKS ABOUT THE HARSHEST LESSON: ACCEPTANCE
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Iqbaal Ramadhan talks about growing up different, getting pressured, and meeting his first love. As a very talented actor who is also passionate about music, Iqbaal Ramadhan has won the hearts of millions of people. He started his career at a young age. He spent his childhood as a member of one of Indonesia's talented boy bands at that time. But, it doesn't stop there. He gained more and more popularity from his leading role in numerous successful movies. No matter what he does, it seems like he will always have his ways of getting showered with love from his fans. Today, we are getting up close and personal with Iqbaal, talking about how he makes his way in life, from his debut until his work today, and what gets in the way. Listen now only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 147 Ade Putri TALKS ABOUT BEYOND A FULL PLATE
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Ade Putri talks about not being introduced well to food, leaving work and a kick-ass son. The culinary world does not only revolves around the food and beverage businesses and professional chefs. There is one profession in the culinary industry that not everyone knows about, and it is what Ade Putri has been doing for quite some time now, a culinary storyteller. It’s more than just telling food stories. Becoming a culinary storyteller requires lots of abilities because just having a sharp sense of taste is not enough. Now, we are digging up her journey on how she entered the culinary world, what’s left behind, and the one thing that keeps her from doing what she loves the most. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 146 Pandu Sjahrir TALKS ABOUT BEING USEFUL NOT USE-LESS
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Pandu Sjahrir talks about not playing with money, never a loan from his father and investing in nature. Pandu Sjahrir is one of Southeast Asia’s leading investors who needs no introduction. He serves as the director, head, board member and chairman for several leading companies from the sector of technology to the coal mining industry. In addition to all those reputable positions, he works in multiple organizations to promote entrepreneurship, education and investment in Southeast Asia. Today, Pandu shares all his business journey, from where it all begins to where he is now. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 145 Eva Celia TALKS ABOUT GENERATING MUSIC FOR THE WORLDWIDE MARKET
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Eva Celia talks about not trying to impress anyone, reaching out to the global audience and taking the needed break. Actress, model, singer-songwriter Eva Celia is well known for her talents and abilities in the public eyes. Growing up, highly influenced by the music she heard at home, she chose to be in the industry without any pressure. She is passionate about what she’s doing and always gives her all in everything, but at the end of the day, she knows when to stop, breathe, and start again. Now, we are listening to her complete story on her career, the experiences that have shaped her, turning points that have challenged her, and what we’re expecting from her soon. Listen now, only on Spotify.

episode_name: Pod. 144 Bam Mastro TALKS ABOUT THE ROAD TO GLOBAL LISTENERS
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Bam Mastro Talks about meeting his worst mental state, speaking locally and what’s next for EK.  Bam Mastro is a singer-songwriter and music producer. Moreover, he is best known for his role as the lead vocalist for Indonesian indie band, Elephant Kind. During his career he had to overcome several obstacles on his musical triumph, that is definitely not easy to deal with. Today, we will hear about his lowest point of life that made him who he is today, his point of view on the global market, and revealing the next chapter for Elephant Kind. Get ready to know the what lies behind the eccentric side of Bam Mastro. Listen now, only on Spotify.

episode_name: Pod. 143 Danny Masrin TALKS ABOUT WHAT IT TAKES TO BE THE NUMBER ONE GOLFER IN THE COUNTRY
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Danny Masrin talks about 18 holes with Lee Westwood, the olympics, and how it all started. For the past year, golf gains burst of popularity during the pandemic. Somehow, the silver lining found amidst the crisis is that it helps golf to bounce back in the country. Danny Masrin is a professional golfer, a brand ambassador for numerous brands, and safe to say, he is the best player in the country. This episode, Danny will reveal the real reasons on why he has chosen to follow his passion for golf, how it all begins and how it brings him to the olympics. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 142 TALKS ABOUT A DISCUSSION ON BRINGING THE WORLD TO LOCAL NARRATIVES
description: In today’s episode, we talk about Ali’s new family, pleasing the global audience and breaking boundaries to entertain the world.  An in-depth discussion on how local stories can resonate with and be delivered to a global audience, as well as efforts that we can all do to support the growth of the local film industries with Lucky Kuswandi the Director of Ali & Ratu Ratu Queens, Muhammad Zaidy & Meiske Taurisia the Producers of Palari Films, Shanty Harmayn from BASE Entertainment, and Netflix’s Director of Content for Southeast Asia, Malobika Banerji. Listen now, only on Spotify!  Taken from a live online event held on the 23 June 2021.

episode_name: Pod. 141 Tarra Budiman TALKS ABOUT FINDING THE ATTENTION NEEDED
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Tarra Budiman talks about the two mentors, no financial plans and never stop shining bright. Tarra Budiman is an Indonesian actor, model and host. He began his career in 2005 when he tried his luck in modeling and started joining casting calls for local tv series. Nowadays, Tarra is focusing on how to avoid the thought of the pandemic taking over young artists’ works. He is also focused on finding ways to make others happy. In this episode, he shared all of his personal stories, what he looks forward in the future, all the good things, bad things, and everything in between. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 140 Swain Mahisa TALKS ABOUT BEING YOUNG, REBELLIOUS AND CHOOSING THE RIGHT PATH
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Swain Mahisa talks about getting tricked, investing in his teens and figuring out what he wants.   Swain Mahisa started off at an early age into his career, but that doesn’t mean that he doesn’t have enough to bring to the table. At his current age, Swain has shouldered many talents, starting with the success of his business to the success of his music career, he is known for the amount of give that he brings to everything he does. In this episode, Swain will be uncovering his principles, investing and many more. Listen up, cause it’s gonna be a good one. Listen now, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 139 Pandji Pragiwaksono TALKS ABOUT THE RISE OF COMEDY WITH FAKE LAUGHTERS
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Pandji Pragiwaksono talks about switching plans, starting a business and making sure the tour runs this time.   Pandji Pragiwaksono is an Indonesian stand-up comedian, actor, radio broadcaster and a man that upholds many other titles, who has colored our screens through all these years. Started off his career as a radio host, Pandji now creates beautiful moments for all of us by eliciting laughter from the audience he meets. Today, we covered all about his plans of getting into business, behind the rise of comedy in Indonesia, and many more. Listen now, only on Spotify!

description: In this episode of Makna Talks, Rapot talks about a whole load of dramas, pleasing the ear and unforgettable moments.  Rapot (Reza, Anka, Radhini & Abigail) are a group of entertaining & talented individuals, combined into making one explosive podcast. episode_name: Kelas Puber S2 Ep 10: Bener Kata Mas Ray....
description: Gak disangka setelah sehala drama yang harus mereka lewati, Puput, Rasta, Ajay, dan Mahmud bisa kumpul bareng-bareng lagi. Untuk mengingat perjalanan mereka selama ini, mereka memutuskan buat pergi ke pantai sebagai cara agar mereka bisa refreshing! Tapi kok, yang niatnya buat seneng-seneng malah jadi lesu karena berasa ada yang hilang. Akhirnya, setelah banyak galau, mereka memutuskan untuk mencari cara biar bisa ketemu sama Mas Ray. Gimana caranya ya? Mas Ray tuh sebenernya kemana aja sih?  Biar makin mantep, jangan lupa pake earphone ya. Dengarkan episode hari ini di Spotify!

episode_name: Kelas Puber S2 Ep 9: Rasta Nge-Twist
description: Rasta ini emang beda. Ibarat plot twist di pilem-pilem, udah klimaks banget cerita hidupnya. Setelah sukses viral di Twitter, Rasta kedapetan client papan atas, yaitu untuk membantu kampanye teh Caleg geulis nan BM-an. Tapi ya namanya juga pilem holywings, pasti ada percikan-percikan plot twist. Ditengah puncak kesuksesan Rasta, tiba-tiba si lima sekawan didatangi polisi, dan mengubah kehidupan Rasta 180 derajat seketika itu juga. Kira-kira apa yang terjadi? Gimana nasib karir Rasta? Apakah akan berhenti sampai disini aja?   Biar makin mantep, jangan lupa pake earphone ya. Dengarkan episode hari ini di Spotify!

episode_name: Kelas Puber S2 Ep 8: Apa Adanya Untuk Ada Apanya
description: Karena ditolak dari wawancara pekerjaan, Mahmud memutuskan untuk ambil kelas bahasa inggris biar gak di tolak lagi sama perusahaan-perusahaan lain. Eh yang awalnya dia kira jadi masalah besar, malah membawa kebaikan. Kapan lagi coba bisa les bahasa inggris sekaligus ketemu cewe cantik selagi kelas? Tapi ternyata, bukan Mahmud doang yang dapet manfaatnya, Mahmud juga bisa bermanfaat buat orang lain. Katanya sih belajar bahasa inggris paling ampuh kalo latihan ngobrol sama orang. Gimana Mud? Udah siap belom ngobrol sama bule? Biar makin mantep, jangan lupa pake earphone ya. Dengarkan episode hari ini di Spotify!

episode_name: Kelas Puber S2 Ep 7 : Bisnis Jalur Belakang
description: Akhirnya dateng juga waktunya Ajay untuk tes capenes! Walaupun persiapan pas-pasan, gapapa deh gas aja. Eh tapi, pas dateng ke tempat tes kok malah ada hal lain yang lebih menarik? Emang bener sih, jadi Penes gaada yang bisa ngalahin, tapi bisnis jalur belakang kok menggirukan banget ya? Sebenernya apasih yang menarik perhatiannya Ajay? Let’s make some money!    Biar makin mantep, jangan lupa pake earphone ya. Dengarkan episode hari ini di Spotify!

episode_name: Kelas Puber S2 Ep 6 : Cantik Gampang Kerja
description: Siapasih yang gatau Puput? Cewe cantik yang bisa membuat semua kepala laki-laki nengok. Tapi, siapa bilang jadi cantik itu mudah? Buat Puput, awalnya sih memang mudah. Dapet perhatian baik dari banyak orang, mudah dapet kerjaan, she’s living the life! Tapi makin lama kok gak segampang itu ya jadi orang cantik? Bener gak sih kalo orang cantik mudah dimanfaatin? Yang tadinya mau kerja serius, jadi ribet deh. Yuk buka halaman baru Put!   Biar makin mantep, jangan lupa pake earphone ya. Dengarkan episode hari ini di Spotify!

description: Yang awalnya cuman nemenin Mami ke pasar, eh akhirnya cari kerjaan. Siapa sih yang gak kenal sikap santai nya Rasta? Dari dosen sampe temen kelas, semuanya udah kenal pasti sama Rasta and his iconic “ya pasti ada jalannya”. Akhirnya, si Rasta yang serba santuy ini harus ngerasain pahit pahit nya dunia kerja guys karena semua butuh uang! Kira-kira bisa ga ya Rasta dapet pekerjaan dengan sifat unik nya itu? Eh terus ini kenapa notif Twitter rame banget ya? Emang rezeki gak kemana.  Biar makin mantep, jangan lupa pake earphone ya. Dengarkan episode hari ini di Spotify!

description: Biasanya kalau lagi tidur pulas dibangunin sama telpon suka ada aja yang aneh-aneh. Itulah yang Mahmud alami di episode kali ini. description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Herjunot Ali talks about going broke, a change in perspective, and being more than just a look Herjunot Ali, or mostly known as Junot, is an Indonesian actor born and raised in Jakarta. description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Laze talks about not being called a local gem, the freestyle days and finding the ways to be appreciated. Laze is an Indonesian based rapper with the goal to create an easy-listening hiphop music for all.  With his new album “Puncak Janggal”, Laze tells the story of someone who always wants to reach the top & learns how to adapt, just like how he has since he was a kid. Learning that being in the music industry is not all about rainbows & sunshine, Laze is here to talk about striving, thriving & learning to be more. Listen to our conversation, only on Spotify.

description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Erwin Gutawa talks about the perfect combination, the good old 2000s, and not being called a legend. It is an understatement to call him a maestro when it comes to music arranging. With his sharp taste & unique touch on compossing, he has brough the whole industry on a new level. On this episode of Makna Talks, Erwin Gutawa is here to show it all from his personal opinions, his journey, his past and many more. It’s never too late to commemorate National Music Day by listening to Erwin Gutawa’s new album, Symphonesia, available on all digital platform. Listen to our conversation, only on Spotify.

description: A conversation in collaboration with @digimap_id, we sat down with Soleh Solihun. Soleh, born and raised in Bandung, is an astonishing entertainer who has filled our screens & radios with laughter. Starting from his stories when he first came to Jakarta to report a story, to his principals in writing, and even talking about the scenes behind his creations. We talked about his views about the death of written journalism, how he ask cold questions, and taking advantage of technology into his works. Soleh Solihun is here to once again, entertain us all is his own way.  🌟GIVEAWAY ALERT  We’re giving away IDR 2.000.000 MAP Vouchers for 4 lucky winners! Go to our Youtube channel to participate. Giveaway will be closed on 26 January at 10 AM and winners will be announced at 5 PM that day. Good luck!

episode_name: Pod. 125 Marissa Anita TALKS ABOUT SLOW LIVING IN THE HUSTLE
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Marissa Anita talks about cutting off interactions, a decade of acting, and choosing the life she wants. Marissa Anita, a face that has decorated our TV screens with her bright & intellectual anchoring, is here to talk about making choices on her life. Balancing many titles starting from Journalist, to News Anchor, to Actress, might be tough for many, but Marissa is here to talk about how she does so herself. Currently casted in Quarantine Tales the movie @bioskoponlineid @filmquarantinetales that talks about the stories from 5 directors, Marissa Anita continues to inspire us with her personal tales. Listen now, only on Spotify

episode_name: Pod. 124 Nino Kayam TALKS ABOUT THE UNPLANNED BENEFACTION
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Nino Kayam talks about wasting resources, accepting the moments and making good use of it. Anindyo Baskoro or known better as Nino Kayam is the N-word that we all sing to when we talk about RAN. We all probably know how they come about but in today's episode, we talked about how Nino stayed in what he believes and how achievements aren't the reason to keep on going but to learn and adapt to what the people want. After 15 years with RAN and 7 years with LaleIlmanNino, we can only imagine the fun and hard work that applies. listen now, only on Spotify.

episode_name: Pod. 123 Enzy Storia TALKS ABOUT TURNING FEARS TO LAUGHTERS
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Enzy Storia talks about dealing with insecurities, taking chances and conversations backstage  No better way for us to start the year with a brand new episode featuring Enzy Storia, the lady that kept you entertained throughout 2020 as a part of The Tonight Show. On this episode, you can still hear her classic laughter but we took it a step further and talked about more important stuffs like how she finally found the courage to encounter her weakness and fear of insecurities. We hope this episode can start off your year better than it was last year. Happy New Year to all of you!

episode_name: Pod. 122 Gita Wirjawan TALKS ABOUT LOOKING FOR LUCKY NARRATORS FOR THE LONG GAME
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Gita Wirjawan talks about not running for politics, gambling on ideas and keeping up with the youth. Merry Christmas from us at Makna Talks and on this special day instead of the bearded man in red, we have Gita Wirjawan with us to spread the message of positivity. Gita Wirjawan was once the Minister of Trade of the Republic of Indonesia or as the man would say, he was once in public service. Today, pak Gita is an Indonesian entrepreneur, investment banker, philanthropist and also a podcast host called Endgame. Listen to today's podcast to know why you should start reading and what it takes to become the narrator for the long game. Available only on Spotify.

episode_name: Pod. 121 Luna Maya TALKS ABOUT DOING EVERYTHING SEAMLESSLY IN ONE TAP
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Luna Maya talks about the biggest blessing, being relevant and the power in her hand. Luna Maya started just over 20 years ago in this entertaining industry when probably most of you were out there making a mess in the kitchen. From the cover of magazines to companying your breakfast on morning music shows, Luna have done it all. You will hear how Luna try to keep it up to the social standards and lowering down egos to still make it relevant. We partner up with @samsungindonesia to discover how Luna can seamlessly work and enjoy the K-dramas, all in one tap. Available only on Spotify. Elevate how you work & play with #GalaxyNote20 series. Visit www.galaxylaunchpackcom.

episode_name: Pod. 120 Afgan TALKS ABOUT THE HOLDUP THAT WAS NEEDED
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Afgan talks about skipping auditions, the fans and being back with a healthier state of mind. What’s your Afgan song story? We believe you’ve jammed on one or two during your high or lows but today we get to know how it all started. From skipping auditions for The Cure to being back from a needed hiatus. Afgansyah Reza is here on Makna Talks to talk all about it. Only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 119 Rachel Amanda TALKS ABOUT BEING CORNERED OVER PRIVILEGES
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Rachel Amanda talks about growing up in the industry, the pressures and #KitaSemuaSahabat When you were out there making scenes in a shopping mall asking for toys, Rachel Amanda Aurora was acting scenes after scenes as a child. With over 50 works, Amanda is still considered as Indonesia’s most talented actress and we teamed up with @cerdasberkarakter.kemdikbudri to talk about the pressures at home, school and work. Here is a podcast to understand the danger of bullying. Only on Spotify. - You are never alone. Report any bullying case you see or experience through @kemdikbud.ri: Call: 177  Email: pengaduan@kemdikbud.go.id Online form: http://ult.kemdikbud.go.id/publik/form/pengaduan

episode_name: Pod. 118 Cantika Abigail TALKS ABOUT TEMPORARY SEPARATIONS
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Cantika Abigail talks about the day she was told to leave, building confidence and asking for a sign.  You may know her as a part of a trio that once was made to entertain many of us and they exactly did what they were supposed to do. on top of their career, they were asked to go their own ways and today we meet the confident, brave and brand new soloist, Cantika Abigail. Out here to talk about her latest release but ended up with a conversation about body positivity and building confidence. Get your ears ready for this week's episode only on Spotify.

episode_name: Pod. 117 Erastus Radjimin TALKS ABOUT BEING THE DUMBEST IN THE ROOM
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Erastus Radjimin talks about game changing hospitality, taking no salary and waiting for the light after the dark. Erastus “erry” Radjimin fell in love with the world of hospitality despite being introduced to hotels as a boy. From what started as a personal joy, he now owns 17 hotels in Indonesia that started off with his first, known best as Artotel. Today, things are better than it was a few months ago. Sales dropped by 80 percent and a 10% occupancy was considered as a good day. Listen to today’s podcast to know just how much Covid-19 have affected him as a bright and young CEO.  Only on Spotify.

episode_name: Pod. 116 Andrea Gunawan TALKS ABOUT STEPPING UP YOUR ONLINE DATING GAME
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Andrea Gunawan talks about dating in 2020, misconception of online dating and seeking common ground. What’s a better way to find your ideal online date with a few tips and tricks by the love guru we all love, Andrea Gunawan aka Catwomanizer. On this episode, we teamed up with Ok Cupid for the advice we didn’t know we all needed for dating in 2020 and broke some misconceptions. Unlike our podcast with Catwomanizer 2 years ago, hopefully you’ll find love on your first swipe!  Only on Spotify. #MaknaxOkCupid

episode_name: POD.115 Moshe Panjaitan TALKS ABOUT THE TRANSFORMATIONAL TECHNOLOGY THAT WILL CHANGE THE WORLD
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Moshe Panjaitan talks about the third internet wave, persuading the boomers, and being in a bit of a rush. Internet of Things may sound easy to understand but it's much more complicated than what you think. Although they said the same thing about the internet a few decades ago. We talked with Moshe Panjaitan CEO of Miota International Teknologi to explain how this technology works and how it can change the way we live better by using the internet. This podcast is so interesting and fascinating, it will make you want to skip a few years to see it in action. Available only on Spotify.

episode_name: POD.114 Hannah Al Rashid TALKS ABOUT BREAKING THE SILENCE ON SEXUAL VIOLENCE
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Hannah Al Rashid talks about raising the voice for her, fighting for logic, and #GerakBersama In the beginning, Hannah Al Rashid left London to Indonesia when she was going to apply for work at the United Nations Development Program (UNDP), but it didn’t happen and instead, she was offered to become a model in a video clip. Thankfully she took the gig. After countless roles in movies, now she uses her fame as a platform to voice out against gender inequality and improving lives through inspiring stories. Just like today, she inspired us with her story as we teamed up with Pusat Penguatan Karakter Kementerian Pendidikan dan Kebudayaan RI to talk about our fight against sexual violence in Indonesia. A conversation across the globe, all the way from the UK, only on Spotify. Go to #GerakBersama on all social media handles for more information about resources, communities, and organisations working on sexual violence

episode_name: POD.113 Nadya Hutagalung TALKS ABOUT SAVING OUR GREATEST THREAT, MANKIND.
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Nadya Hutagalung talks about the escape, meeting the holiness, and saving lives from losing one.  The beautiful Nadya Hutagalung took the flight to Tokyo and began her modeling journey at the age of 12. What started as a school holiday went on for 4 years and became one of her first job in the industry. That was before she became an MTV VJ in 1995, when she had to escape Australia to Singapore with a police escort. Just when you thought it couldn’t get any worse, Nadya finds out that her lover at that time took his own life. With all the lows she has faced as a single mom, it all made her stronger as a mother of three. Listen to today’s podcast to know how, only on Spotify.

episode_name: POD. Spesial Sumpah Pemuda: Youth Leadership
description: In case you missed out our takeover at @hardrockfm earlier today,  it's now out on Spotify! to celebrate sumpah pemuda we teamed up with @ideafestid and talked with @hadiismanto__ and @miobyrda about youth leadership.

episode_name: POD. 112 Princess Megonondo TALKS ABOUT THE FAST PACE GENERATION
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Princess Megonondo talks about the night that changed her, the friendly competition in life, and the importance of university.  Princess Megonondo was made Miss Indonesia in 2019 after successfully winning Miss Jambi in the same year but that didn't stop her from going forward and finishing the top 40 during the Miss World contest in 2019. Today, Princess has passed on her crown but continues to do good especially at University in Binus International. We teamed up with Binus International to discuss how important is a healthy education institution for the fast pace generation and how their latest academic system can change the game of taking two degrees without flying abroad. A very helpful and interesting conversation, available on Spotify. Learn more about @binusinter or go to their website: international.binus.ac.id #limitlessfuture #binusinternational #binusinterxmaknatalks

episode_name: POD. 111 Kai & Manda TALKS ABOUT THE DIGITAL REVOLUTION OF TRANSACTIONS
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Kai & Manda talks about the rise of values in coins, investing in the future and an introduction to Tokocrypto. Most likely you've heard the term Cryptography, but after watching multiple videos about what it is, you still don't get it, do you? well, let us help you out and explain not only what it is, but to get you started in investing on your first Crypto Assets. We teamed up with Tokocrypto to discuss the future of digital transactions and making sure being fooled isn't going to happen to us. Listen to today's episode only on Spotify and head on to @tokocrypto's Instagram to learn more.

episode_name: Pod. 110 Podkesmas TALKS ABOUT THE ONE YEAR WHEN EVERYTHING CHANGED
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Podkesmas talks about the four characters, taking it all seriously and the future strategies. The squad may not be back on their podcast, but they are here at ours. Taking a quick break just before kicking off season 4 of Podkesmas. A visit to our HQ was filled with conversations about the beginning, taking the jokes aside and the possibilities of expansion with Ananda Omesh, Angga Nggok, Surya Insomnia and Imam Darto. Check out today’s podcast only on Spotify and make sure you wish them a happy anniversary!

episode_name: Pod. 109 Pamungkas TALKS ABOUT THE DREAMS AND DEDICATION
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Pamungkas talks about the drastic changes, healing a broken heart and the sweat of doing it all alone. No, not the football player but the talented singer, producer and songwriter Pamungkas. Without a doubt he is currently the biggest in the game when it comes to music in Indonesia. Despite the fact that he has no answer to how this all happened, check out today’s episode to know how hard this all takes, one note at a time. Only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 108 Bintang Emon TALKS ABOUT THE GREAT MOMENTS THAT TAKES TIME
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Bintang Emon talks about the stand up dream, trapped in a strip club and learning to let go. There is a man in charged of keeping us entertained during this pandemic strike, his name is Bintang Emon. The stand-up comedian that everyone were talking about for the past year. Although you’ve seen him on your Instagram and family group chat on WhatsApp, in real life, Bintang is the kind of kid your mother wants you to be. His hardworking and life changing stories will keep your jaw drop for the next hour. Listen now! Only on Spotify.

episode_name: Pod. 107 Adinia Wirasti TALKS ABOUT PLAYING ROLES FOR THE CHANGE WE SEEK
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Adinia Wirasti talks about her faith in film, the rough beginning, and saying yes to #eyesaidyes. Many of us adore Adinia Wirasti not only because she starred in the most popular high-school flick in 2002, but because of Adinia’s intelligence, her friendly personality off camera, and her big heart for donating her cornea at @lionseyebankjakarta. You can talk for hours about the books she reads, the different roles she played, or how she started off as a bully victim at school. All in today’s podcast, only on Spotify!

episode_name: Pod. 106 Andhyta F. Utami TALKS ABOUT RAISING A VOICE, NOT SEA LEVEL
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Andhyta F. Utami talks about fighting the facts, the threats we live in, and finding the right solution.  Andhyta Firselly Utami or Afu is the type of person you’d be compared to by your parents. Her studies abroad, writings, and intelectual presence is felt even without her saying a word. There is a lot in what Afu does, but she prefers being called as an environmental economist and pun expert. This episode, we spoke about the truth, the sad and dirty facts of what’s happening today, and tons of other reasons for you to join the conversation, only on Spotify.

episode_name: Pod.105 Iga Massardi TALKS ABOUT NOT BEING ABLE TO LINK TO THE GENERATION
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Iga Massardi talks about being overlapped, risking it all, and the tough life of Kota Bekasi. Iga Massardi is an Indonesian musician, vocalist, producer, and guitarist of Barasuara. He was also the guitarist for Tika and The Dissindents, The Trees and the Wild, and Soulvibe. But to keep it simple, Iga is the man who's responsible in making Batik looks good on stage. In today's episode, Iga speaks the truth about making music and what it takes to make your childhood dreams of being a rockstar come alive.

episode_name: Pod.104 Fatih Respati TALKS ABOUT BEATING TALENTS WITH HARDWORK
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Fatih Respati talks about being a student before becoming an athlete, no place for fun, and pure hard work.  Fatih Respati isn't your regular high school neighbor, he’s in to win it all the way in the United States. Unlike many students out here, Fatih is out there making his name to the top of the league carrying Indonesian flag on his back by playing basketball. But in this episode, he explains why being a student-athlete isn't always fun and how is he putting his life as a student first before being an athlete.

episode_name: Pod.103 Mikha Angelo TALKS ABOUT BEING AN AMATEUR ONCE
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Mikha Angelo talks about making music for others, stepping out of the zone, and apologizing. Mikha Angelo is a musical genius that plays, writes, and produces music for top names of the country from Raisa to, Fatin, to Rendy Pandugo and the list goes on. The 22 year old always knew that this is the industry that he will grow but it hasn't been that easy from being known as as the XFactor boy, to the overtunes and now releasing his debut solo album: Amateur. Listen to today's podcast to hear all about it and stream his album now!

episode_name: Pod.102 DEDDY CORBUZIER TALKS ABOUT ENDING THE ERA OF MAGIC
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Deddy Corbuzier talks about the threat of free speech, disliking the past and sacrifices. Deddy Corbuzier is probably your go to podcast host to hear about the latest controversies on the web, from politic related news, public figures fighting over personal matters or people apologizing for their mistakes. But before his successful YouTube channel, Deddy was known as a mentalist and professional illusionist winning awards worldwide and made history for his television show. Listen to today’s episode if you want to know why he said goodbye to the world of magic and what are his plans ahead.

In today’s Independence Day special episode, we bring you a legend for many of us, the talented Rossa. You've probably heard her from your mother’s go-to jams, your go-to karaoke song, or probably from TikTok videos that people dance along to. Rossa remains to be one of the most popular artists in Indonesia and other countries, she also became one of the best selling Indonesian artists of all time based on her album sales and sold over 10 million copies in the region. But all that success isn't what the world meant to her. Listen to today’s podcast to figure out what she wants to do next. Today’s episode is in several parts with a very special experience. So head over to "Spesial 17an Makna Talks & Rossa" playlist on Spotify now!

episode_name: Pod.101 HAMISH DAUD TALKS ABOUT LIFE IN THE DEEP BLUE
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Hamish Daud talks about getting hit in the head, growing up chasing barrels with a legend and now, settling down. Hamish Daud is an architect, actor, presenter, recently a father, and the founder of IOP (Indonesian Ocean Pride). Born in Australia, Hamish have always been beach hopping in many parts of Indonesia from a young boy. In fact, he was whale watching when we were all back at home comfortable in our sofas. In today's episode, you get to hear how all the adventures make him a man today. Only on Makna Talks.

episode_name: Pod.100 Basuki Tjahaja Purnama TALKS ABOUT STARTING ALL OVER AGAIN.
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Basuki Tjahaja Purnama talks about being locked up, conversations with the Almighty, and starting a band.  Basuki Tjahaja Purnama is an Indonesian businessman, politician, and former governor of Jakarta. But to some, he is a hero. On 27 September 2016, while introducing a government project to citizens of the Thousand Islands, he said some citizens would not vote for him because they were being "threatened and deceived" by those using the verse of a Quran, which leads to Islamist mass protest that took place on 4 November 2016 in Jakarta and led to his imprisonment. Today he is a free man and more than ever, this is the new start of Basuki Tjahaja Purnama.
Welcome to an all-new season of Makna Talks, In case you’re new here Makna Talks is a weekly podcast of candid conversations and welcome to our trailer.

episode_name: Pod.99 PUTRI TANJUNG TALKS ABOUT BEING THE CHOSEN ONE
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Putri Tanjung talks about not having to impress anyone, defying the odds and living to her own expectations.  Putri Tanjung is the Founder of Creativepreneur and other businesses that she and her partners work on but for the past 6 months, she is known to be one of President Joko Widodo's Presidential Staffs. Many are saying that this wasn't a surprise as she is also the daughter of a successful businessman, Chairul Tanjung. But that's not the case, listen to today's podcast to hear the story from the lady herself and what is it like to be one of the busiest people at the age of 23 years old.

episode_name: Pod. 98 ARIAN ARIFIN TALKS ABOUT BAND TO BURGERS.
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Arian Arifin talks about stigmas in the 80s, being a city boy, and not getting older.   If you haven't heard their music or saw their merchandise worn everywhere, then at least, you must have eaten their big sized juicy burgers. Arian Arifin or Arian Tigabelas is the man behind all that. He started a band in 1992 called Puppen and ended it in 2002. he then started another band called Seringai which is probably one of the most well-known rock bands in Indonesia today. If you're interested in how he ended up having his law-less empire, you don't want to miss today's episode of Makna Talks.

episode_name: POD. 97 ANDRA ALODITA TALKS ABOUT CREATING A SYSTEM FOR CHANGE
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Andra Alodita talks about counting steps, listing down happiness, and healing through sweat.  A healthy, well organized and loving mother, we like to think that Andra Alodita has influenced more people than self proclaimed  influencers through her positive posts and neat way of life. However, it never was like that, after figuring it all out in 2020. Check out today’s episode to find out how to stay positive when life gets tough.

episode_name: POD. 96 VIDI ALDIANO TALKS ABOUT TAKING A STAND FOR MUSIC
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Vidi Aldiano talks about survival mode, battling for his wants, and self gratitude.  Oxavia Aldiano or Vidi Aldiano is an Indonesian singer, musician, songwriter, and business owner. You’d probably know him from his hit singles “Status Palsu” or “Nuansa Bening”, taken from the album “Pelangi di Malam Hari“ back in 08’. But today, he’s speaking a bit more than just about teenage love. Vidi released his latest single “Bertahan Melewati Senja” right after he battled with cancer and the voices in his head. Today, Vidi is a much happier man and shared with us what it takes to be in this position today. Head over to Spotify to listen.

episode_name: Pod.95 NICOLINE PATRICIA MALINA TALKS ABOUT ABOUT SELF REALISATION
description: In today’s episode of Makna Talks, Nicoline Patricia talks about making choices, proving yourself right and lowering egos.  Nicoline Patricia Malina is probably your favorite fashion photographer, she has shot for numerous magazines and brands all over the world but it hasn't always been that easy, from sending emails to potential clients to talk with random talents on the bus of Amsterdam. But today, after millions of frames taken and numerous of awards and exhibitions, Nicoline is proud to see her students as new photographers in the industry. Listen to all about it on today’s podcast to know what it means to capture moments and how to make peace with yourself in order to be successful.

episode_name: Pod.94 REZA RAHADIAN TALKS ABOUT NEVER STOPPING.
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Reza Rahadian talks about non-stop productivity, education and a perfect mother.  It’s hard to mention your favorite movies without having Reza Rahadian in it. The Indonesian actor that rose from his debut film in 2004, has gained a lot of respect and awards for over 15 years in the film industry. But it hasn't always been that easy with his struggles in education and that is one of the reasons why he is very vocal about it. Recently, Reza have taken the quarantine days to another level by making a mini series called Sementara Selamanya. Listen to today's podcast to hear all about it.  Makna Talks is only available on Spotify.

episode_name: Pod.93 RIZKY FEBIAN TALKS ABOUT FEELING ALONE IN A CROWD
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Rizky Febian talks about a divorce, saying goodbye forever and the healing of a loneliness.  Rizky Febian is an indonesian musician and songwriter that is making hits over hits every time he uploads a song. The son of the Indonesian comedian, Sule didn't always start his career that way, he was a presenter, actor and a regular boy back in Bandung watching his father joke around on television growing up whilst his mother was working as an artist back in his hometown. Today, he is here to tell us all about it and most importantly, to motivate us in chasing what we really want.   Makna Talks is only available on Spotify.

episode_name: Pod.92 HELMY YAHYA TALKS ABOUT RESURRECTING NATIONAL TELEVISION
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Helmy Yahya talks about giving  back to his core, trips for books and and admiration to a brother. Helmy  Yahya is known as the king of trivias in Indonesia, but many didn't  know behind those fun facts you see on telly, is a bright student and a  loyal son of a hardworking father back in the slums of Sumatra. Helmy  grew up to be a bright star of his schools and as we all know helped us  know most of our pub quizzes. Listen to how it all happened and how it  all ended. Check out today's podcast to hear all about it. Makna Talks is only available on Spotify.

episode_name: KELAS PUBER EP22: MAAF MAAF MAAF
description: Selamat datang di Kelas PUBER - sebuah sketsa kecil tentang kelas online berisi 1 dosen dan 4 mahasiswa, di kelas ini mereka tidak hanya belajar tentang ilmu pengetahuan dasar tetapi juga pembahasan seputar masalah pribadi mereka. Kelas PUBER tayang selama bulan Ramadhan setiap jam 3 pagi untuk menemani kalian sahur dari Senin sampai Jumat. Makna Talks is available on Spotify, Anchor, Apple Podcast, Soundcloud and Youtube Twitter: @maknatalks Instagram: @maknatalks Business: talks@maknagroup.com

episode_name: Pod. 90 NAZLA ALIFA TALKS ABOUT GETTING PAID FOR BEING YOURSELF
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Nazla Alifa talks about trips by Louis, a near-death experience and staying at home. Nazla Alifa is probably your go to gram to look for poses and outfits of the day but behind cheerful Instagram posts, she is as happy as it can be, living the life of travelling and promoting top brands in the world. We also spoke a little bit of how she managed to keep on going even at times when she almost died on a boat. But above all here's a podcast about one of the best jobs in the world. episode_name: Pod.89 DIAN SASTROWARDOYO TALKS ABOUT GOING BEHIND THE SCENES.
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Dian Sastrowardoyo talks about her addiction to K-dramas, a cup of coffee and not acting.  Diandra Paramita Sastrowardoyo or better known as Dian Sastro have starred in movies that you have talked about with everyone in your family. She is a beautiful mother of two that is planning to go beyond acting with her first produced film "Guru Guru Gokil". Although we know a lot about her from previous interviews with tons of medias around, this one is a whole different story. Check it out on today's episode of Makna Talks! episode_name: Pod.88 HANDOKO HENDROYONO TALKS ABOUT LIFE AS A MAKER
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks,  Handoko Hendroyono talks about being relevant, creative confidence and legendary footprints. Handoko Hendroyono has made a huge impact for the world of designers, he's made timeless catchphrases and numerous of ideas for the world of advertising in this country but that's the past. Today, he is the man behind Jakarta's latest hip spot, M-Bloc. He and a couple of his mates is the founder and creative director for the house of locals. But in today's episode we talked more than that, we talked about him as a writer, a founder, an icon for design but moreover as a maker. Listen to today's episode to know all about it.  Makna Talks is available on Spotify, Anchor, Apple Podcast, Soundcloud and Youtube Twitter: @maknatalks åInstagram: @maknatalks Business: talks@maknagroup.com

episode_name: Pod.87 dr. TIRTA TALKS ABOUT TONING DOWN THE VOICE BUT RAISING AWARENESS
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, dr. Tirta Talks about clarifying dramas, consulting the culture and being less tense.  dr. Tirta isn’t your ordinary doctor. He swears, he shouts and loves the street culture more than you think. Lately the controversial local brand enthusiast have tone down a bit due to numerous advices given to him. By whom? Listen to todays podcast to hear how it all began and a little bit of how the pandemic that is happening going to affect the culture. episode_name: Pod.86 MOHAN HAZIAN TALKS ABOUT CLASH OF CULTURE
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Mohan Hazian talks about signs in opening a store, hype clashes and talking shit towards celebrity brands.  Mohan Hazian is the founder of a well known street-wear brand "thanksinsomnia" and for the past few years has become quite an icon for the industry with his infamous pokerface making jokes and all. Hear what he thinks about the industry today and stick around to know who he chooses to collab, block and endorse in a little game we created.  Makna Talks is available on Spotify, Anchor, Apple Podcast, Soundcloud and Youtube  Twitter: @maknatalks Instagram: @maknatalks Business: talks@maknagroup.com

episode_name: Pod.85 SANDIAGA UNO TALKS ABOUT INVESTING IN YOUTH
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Sandiaga Uno talks about believing in local goods, bankruptcy, and potentials.   2018 and 2019 was one heck of a year for Sandiaga. Traveling to more than 1500 areas across Indonesia to voice his promises as a candidate of vice president for the 2019 election. But as we all know, he lost the gig to Joko Widodo. So, what is the Indonesian businessman and Investor doing today? he continues to support local goods and meeting youth with investors to have bigger opportunities in the future and that includes you and your ideas. Listen to today's podcast to hear all about it.   Makna Talks is available on Spotify, Anchor, Apple Podcast, Soundcloud and Youtube   Twitter: @maknatalks Instagram: @maknatalks Business: talks@maknagroup.com

episode_name: Pod.84 SLANK TALKS ABOUT DRUMS, SEX, AND ROCK & ROLL
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Slank talks about a slanking forever, heroin and saying goodbye in Sanur. In 1983, Bimo Setiawan Almachzumi (Bimbim) started a band in an alley called Potlot South Jakarta and after a few name changes and countless formations, fourteen to be exact, here we are with Slank, the biggest rock band in Indonesia with Akhadi Wira Satriaji (kaka) on Vocals, Bimbim on drums, Abdee Negara on guitar, Mohammad Ridwan Hafiedz (Ridho) on guitar and Ivan Kurniawan Arifin (Ivanka) on Bass. They went through a lot in the past 20 years, some are involved in politics, drugs and everything in between. listen to today's podcast to hear what you missed out on in the early 2000s and don't forget to check out their latest (27th) album, Slanking Forever. available on all digital platforms. episode_name: Pod.83 BARRY LIKUMAHUWA TALKS ABOUT THE TRUE FORM OF JAZZ
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Barry Likumahuwa talks about a jazz festival, overlapping family and John 3:16 Barry Likumahuwa is a bass player known to improvise all the time and from an early age, he was brought up by music taught by a bossa nova singer and jazz musician, Benny Likumahuwa as his father. You may dance to the rhythm made by him back in the BLP (Barry Likumahuwa Project) days or his performances on stage every now and then, but today he has a bigger vision. listen to today's podcast to know what is it and make sure you catch Barry next week at Java Jazz 2020. description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Ayla Dimitri talks about creating her own opportunities, inhaling the process and becoming a wife. With her endless poses and uncountable followers on Instagram, Ayla is probably one of the biggest names as a Fashion Influencer today. But it doesn't look as easy or as happy as what we all see. Through the years of working under another individual, Ayla tells us the journey to what she is today. listen on today's episode of Makna Talks to know all about it. episode_name: Pod.81 KUNTO AJI TALKS ABOUT HEALING UNSEEN WOUNDS
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Kunto Aji talks about being a failed accountant, winning against himself and healing.  Kunto Aji is probably the biggest name for a male soloist today after his biggest hit of "Terlalu Lama Sendiri", he shares what it takes to beat himself and grow bigger with his album "Mantra-mantra" that was released in 2018. In today's episode of Makna Talks, Kunto Aji shares his journey for the past 11 years in the industry and talked about everything before all this happened. episode_name: Pod.80 ARDHITO PRAMONO TALKS ABOUT BREAKING HEARTS AND IMPROVISING SWINGS
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Ardhito Pramono talks about being a sweet fuckboy, part-time work and first time acting. Ardhito Pramono is a 24 year old singer and songwriter and a brand new actor. He played his debut film for NKCTHI (Nanti Kita Cerita Tentang Hari Ini) as Kale, and many said that he and Kale is so much alike. listen to this podcast to know what he thinks about that. Also, Ardhito is known for his Jazz genre songs and that's probably why the girls are lining up well for him. Be the first to listen or you'll miss out on many interesting stories of young Ardhito Pramono.
