episode_name: Pod.79 KALLULA HARSYNTA ESTERLITA TALKS ABOUT GOING SOLO FOR ONCE
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Kallula talks about being forced to quit, sound healing and trying out all at once. Kallula is an Indonesian singer/songwriter, despite being known as a part of Kimokal and one of Dipha Barus' angel, not too long ago she released her first single "This Love" available on all digital platforms. You may think like Iyas that Kallula isn't her real name, but find out on today's episode about it.  Also if you're into trips to the moon or sometimes inside pyramids, this one is for you. listen here to figure out what are we talking about.  Makna Talks is available on Spotify, Anchor, Apple Podcast, Soundcloud and Youtube Twitter: @maknatalks Instagram: @maknatalks Business: talks@maknagroup.com

episode_name: Pod.78 ANGGA DWIMAS SASONGKO TALKS ABOUT FEARS OF FAILING
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Angga Dwimas Sasongko talks about  living in the moment, realities of films and a personal touch. Angga Dwimas Sasongko is an Indonesian award winning film director that started from a very young age and just like any success story it all began from a car garage with Visinema only on it's mind. Today  Visinema is no longer a dreamy company, beacause it is home for over 100 film-makers and  created countless films including the recent NKCTHI (Nanti Kita Cerita Tentang Hari Ini). A movie so close to Angga that he said is one of his best work in 15 years. A story first created by Marchella FP and today becomes the first movie in 2020 to hit 1,000,000 viewers in one week. Listen to today's podcast to know all about it and why he's not stopping. Makna Talks is available on Spotify, Anchor, Apple Podcast, Soundcloud and Youtube Twitter: @maknatalks Instagram: @maknatalks Business: talks@maknagroup.com

episode_name: Pod.77 TALKS ABOUT NOT GIVING AN INCH OF CARE with Rizky Firdaus
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Rizky Firdaus talks about his comedy career, financial planning and irresponsible parenting.   Rizky Firdaus Wijaksana or better known as Uus is a stand up comedian, a creator on youtube and also a fellow podcast host. You may know him on movies as he have starred in a couple of them but also you may know him from being boycotted from national television caused by a tweet; but that's only a tiny bit of his controversial personality. All this information you can find out today on this episode and a lot more about the things you don't know about the man himself. Makna Talks is available on Spotify, Anchor, Apple Podcast, Soundcloud and Youtube Twitter: @maknatalks Instagram: @maknatalks Business: talks@maknagroup.com

episode_name: Pod. 76 TALKS ABOUT SCORES IN LIFE with Bambang Pamungkas
description: In today's episode of Makna Talks, Bambang Pamungkas talks about leaving football, breaking records and making it up one spoon at a time.  Bambang Pamungkas was an Indonesian professional footballer who played for Persija Jakarta in the Liga 1 and a former captain for Indonesia's football team. Bambang made his name is South East Asian football when he scored the only goal for Indonesia at the 2002 Tiger Cup semifinal against Malaysia and continues to make 200 more despite calling it an end this year. Today Bambang is known for his amazing public speaking abilities, his hobbies of gaming and taste in Indonesian culinary but in today's episode Bambang tells us what he likes best about what he does after ending his career in football. Find out what on this episode of Makna Talks.

episode_name: Ep. 27 Makna Family Meeting - End of Year
description: Our last episode of the year is here! We track back what 2019 was like with Ellyse Sinsilia, Ernanda Putra and Iyas Lawrence for us and thank each and everyone of you for taking part of our exciting year. Love to all and take care!  See you in 2020.

episode_name: Pod.75 TALKS ABOUT HEADING UP, NOT SWIPING UP with BKR Brothers
description: BKR Brothers talks about changing a name, being on top of the list and why it does not matter.  We sat down with the boys from BKR Brothers, a podcast of three adults sharing stories to keep you company but make sure the kids are away because it gets down and dirty sometimes. There's Bobby Mandela, Molen Kasetra and Ryo Wicaksono and on today's episode. Molen talks about a day to day job and reconnecting with the boys, Ryo shares about working 7 days a week for a 15 years of debt and Bobby's stories of fishing at Duck Down and in the wild. Make sure you become the first to hear the fun!

episode_name: Pod.74 TALKS ABOUT CONTRIBUTING TO THE CULTURE  with Michael Vincent
description: Michael talks about inside the hype, trend forcasting and invincible.  Michael's last interview was with Complex, a conversation about his life in the industry of hype. In today's episode we talked with the man behind Invincible, a street-wear and sneaker boutique from Taiwan and how it all started from working at Bathing Ape, JackThreads and Training Camp. This is a podcast for you who's into the game and a little sneak peak of what 2020 looks like.

episode_name: Pod.73 TALKS ABOUT HOME IN THE SPIRIT OF BEAUTY with Lizzie Parra
description: Lizzie Parra talks about beautypreneurship, breaking records and tap dancing.  Lizzie Parra is one of Indonesia's OG beauty guru, a gifted makeup artist and the pioneer of a local beauty brand based on her personality, known as BLP (By Lizzie Parra). She started off reviewing products on youtube but now there are more people unboxing her products on the web then she is doing them. This episode is an introduction to what her plans are on making a home out of a brand. Hear all about it today!

episode_name: Pod.72 TALKS ABOUT MAKING A DIFFERENCE BY BEING DIFFERENT with Arief Muhammad
description: Arief Muhammad talks about adaptation, business and making a billionare If you were around at times when twitter was the main hype, you most likely laughed to the jokes but didn't know who he was. Arief Muhammad started off being anonymous but today he is known as one of Indonesia's most successful content creator and busniess man. How did that end up? Check out todays episode to hear all about it.

episode_name: Pod.71 TALKS ABOUT BROADCASTING POSITIVITY with Ucita Pohan
description: Talks about being you, loving you, and for you.   On a daily basis for the last 11 years, Ucita Pohan is a radio broadcaster, but beside that, Ucita is also known as an author for her latest book "Bicara Tubuh". She is also a Master of Ceremony mostly for the weekends but day to day on her social media, she is a happy, confident, self loving woman. Ucita is surrounded with words such as self love, positive energy and being true to yourself but in today's episode we figure out wether those characteristics fit with Ucita in real life or not.

episode_name: Pod.70 TALKS ABOUT MAKING CASH IN A FLASH with Jeffry Jouw
description: Jeffry Jouw talks about respect, race and new friends   If you're into the hype, you know who Jeffry Jouw is, or best known as Jejouw. The Chinese-Indonesian kid is a founder and CEO of USS (Urban Sneaker Society). Recently Jejouw had his 4th event and gathered over 40,000 people from all around the country. Listen to how it all began and the journey for Hype!

episode_name: Pod.69 TALKS ABOUT PLAYING WHERE THEY LEFT OFF with Killing me Reunion
description: Killing Me Reunion talks about addiction, brotherhood and a comeback Killing Me Inside is an Indonesian metal-core band from South Jakarta. It’s hard to tell who’s in it now with members frequently leaving from time to time. But in today’s episode, we talked with the OG, the beginning of it all. The Killing Me Reunion with Onadio Leonardo, Raka Cryril and Fauzan “Sansan”. They share stories from the past and their comeback recently that shook the generation of emos from late 2000s. You wouldn’t want to miss today’s episode because it's full of booze, drugs and everything in between.

episode_name: Pod.68 TALKS ABOUT DEALING WITH BRUISES with Nadin Amizah
description: Talks about hating highschool, dealing with a momager and lives of a gemini. Known by her nickname on the Gram as @cakecaine, Nadin Amizah is a talented Indonesian young singer, songwriter. She started covering songs on instagram and was founded by Dipha Barus back in 2017. Nadine now has her own hits and positively making people cry every weekends. This episode of Makna Talks is a story of doubting love, believing in dreams and the unexpected truth about making songs.

episode_name: Pod.67 TALKS ABOUT STORIES OF YOUTH with Program Peduli
description: Talks about a victim of commercial sexual exploitation, life at correctional facilities and second chances. In today's episode, it's a combination of 3 individuals telling their stories. One is Sheila from Program Peduli, a non profit organization designed to improve social inclusion for six of Indonesia’s most marginalised groups. There's Kaka that talked about life behind bars as a 16 year old and witnessing darkness in between light, Lastly, we hear Memel talked about her first job that led her to become a victim of commercial sexual exploitation at the age of 14. All this to remind what the Youth Pledge is all about.

episode_name: Pod.66 TALKS ABOUT ACHIEVING WHAT THE MIND BELIEVES with Adystra Bimo
description: Talks about community, fashion over passion and racing in chaos Adystra Bimo is the Co-founder of Athletica sports agency, Runhood media and Running Rage. Above all he started the trend of community running in Indonesia and continues to do so in different ways. From running long distance, to making athletes great, and talking about what to wear in your next 5K run. In today’s episode Adystra speaks about what makes Jakarta Marathon one of his least favorite race, his impressive academic learnings about sports and what we’re up to this weekend with Makna Coffee. Hear all about it today.

episode_name: Pod.65 TALKS ABOUT LANGUAGE FOR THE SOUL with Mantra Vutura
description: Talks about collaborations, jealousy and authenticity  From a very young age, music have been in their blood, one performed in Java Jazz at the age of 10, one is the son of Addie MS, an Indonesian conductor, producer and composer. Growing up with new music every week is not new for them and being able to create isn't something difficult. But that's not the case about selling it. Tristan Juliano and Zakari Danubrata speaks about being in the industry. the struggle, the jealousy and the way to keep up on today's episode. Hear all about it here.

episode_name: Pod.64 TALKS ABOUT THE PAST AND THE CURIOUS with Rachel Vennya
description: Talks about sensation, honesty and friends that become family.  You either know her from her 64 million donut story, her endless instagram posts, trendy dishes being sold, or the mother of a cute boy, Xabiru. Rachel Vennya have come a long way to what she calls an achievement. From her dark past and rough childhood, all is said on today's episode. Make sure you check it out!

episode_name: Pod.63 TALKS ABOUT GETTING LOST WITH IDEAS with Naya Anindita
description: Talks about Sci-fi, Mata Najwa and Eggnoid  Back when youtube series weren’t a thing you probably heard a series called “Jalan Jalan Men” that featured Naya with her now husband, Petra a.k.a Jebraw. But despite her love with the outdoors and being filmed, Naya have directed a few movies including “Sundul gan” A movie about Kaskus’ early days and also a movie called “Berangkat!”. We sat down to talk about the most recent one, Eggnoid coming to cinema this December. Listen why you should be the first to watch and how you can be a difference to the world of moving images in this country.

episode_name: Pod.62 TALKS ABOUT THE LONG WAY UPHILL with Yura Yunita
description: Talks about his new hopes, being strong and deadly prisoners.  Yura Yunita is a 28 year old Indonesian singer and songwriter that grew up in Bandung, West Java. Having succeeded with the hits of Cinta dan Rahasia, Harus Bahagia, Intuisi, Buka Hati and many others, Yura Recently celebrated the one year anniversary of her second album “Merakit”. In todays episode we talked about what the year have been for her and stories that will touch you to the bones. Hear now all about it and stick around for a story of Yura in Indonesia’s most dangerous prison visit.

episode_name: Pod.61 TALKS ABOUT BEING A PART TIME ENTERTAINER FULL TIME DAD with Imam Darto
description: Talks about his rides, high school memories and being a love consultant  Imam Darto is a Presenter, Actor, dangdut singer, screenwriter and an ex legendary (as he would say himself) radio host. Despite writting for Pretty Boys, Imam Darto is a father of three and a husband of an understanding wife. I say understanding because Darto treats his family mostly when he’s up to something and lately he’s planning a few adventurous trips. Hear all about it on today’s episode of MaknaTalks.

episode_name: Pod.60 TALKS ABOUT QUESTIONING WHY with Rendy Pandugo
description: Talks about his first love, being in the game and growth  Rendy is an Indonesian singer-songwriter, guitarist and a father of one. By 2016 he moved from playing regulars from cafe to cafe to focusing on his solo career and since then he has released The Journey in 2017 that includes “Silver rain” and “I don’t care” as one of the hits. He came a long way from the days of Soundcloud to who he is today. He stopped by Makna Talks to talk more than just lovesongs but to ask why. Why is it everything that the world offer seems too dark to understand that will feature in his newest single coming soon. Hear all about it now!

episode_name: Pod.59 TALKS ABOUT NATURAL REHABILITATION with Dipha Barus
description: Talks about being a pioneer, anxiety and spread love not drugs  Dipha’s early life wasnt about making people dance but being a family foundation for a struggling life in the middle of an extreme depression. In today’s episode we talked with Dipha Barus, a DJ and music producer that makes people dance around the globe. He recently got back from the States and a show at Melbourne where the dance floor was packed. Hear what it’s like to bring music alive with a substance called nothing but love.

episode_name: Pod.58 TALKS ABOUT ADVENTURES EVERYDAY with Ayudia & Ditto
description: Talks about investments, moving out and thrill seeking  The little family of a content creator and musician is always portrayed happy on the web but are they really that cute offline? We sat down with Ayudia & Ditto to talk about keeping the chemistry alive everyday. The family of three is filled with unique facts especially their fun concept of saving money for happiness. Hear all about it on today’s episode of Makna Talks.

episode_name: Ep. 26 Makna Family Meeting - Tri Mas Nyetir
description: In this episode of Makna Family Meeting, we have a fun announcement. A trip of three boys heading to Bali with their old arse motorbikes. Listen all about it to be a part of their journey.

episode_name: Pod.57 TALKS ABOUT NEW MEDIA with Najwa Shihab, Fellexandro Ruby & Ario Pratomo (LIVE)
description: A special episode that featured our friends from 30 Days of Lunch (Fellexandro Ruby & Ario Pratomo) and Najwa Shihab hosted by NarasiTV for their upcoming festival called Playfest 2019. Hear this episode for inspirations and a little bit of everything.

episode_name: Pod.56 TALKS ABOUT INDEPENDENCE with Oi (Swara Gembira)
description: Talks about freedom, Guruh Soekarno Putra, and the importance of today.   Oi is known from the well made Swara Gembira theatrical performance that features musicians, designers, music directors and dancers across Indonesia. On today’s special podcast we talked about the importance of Independence Day, the first meet up with Guruh Soekarno Putra and what Swara Gembira is all about. The 8th performance will be held in Plaza Senayan Taman Tirta Tengah where we all come to hang out by the fountain, the acts will be held next week on the 23rd of August. Check out http://swaragembira.com/ for more information.

episode_name: Pod.55 TALKS ABOUT TAKING THE LEAP with Najwa Shihab
description: Talks about an offer, having independency, and the power of information.   Najwa Sihab was a news anchor, today a presenter, a digital media founder of NarasiTV, a mother and everything that defines a strong Indonesian woman. We teamed up with Narasi and sat down with Najwa to talk about the beginning of her career and what it takes to be a woman with strong opinions. We also figured out how not intimidating she really is, a little bit about politics and 2 fun facts you would not believe. Catch her around at Playfest 2019 this coming weekend where you can grab the tickets on their website!

episode_name: Pod.54 TALKS ABOUT BEING IN TWO GENERATIONS with Darbotz
description: Talks about the name, the monster, and the process.   You may heard of him or seen his work out and about but rarely you recognise Darbotz. The faceless man is an internationally known graffiti and street artist. His well known Monster "cumi"  is a trademark from his artworks that started from high school. In this podcast we teamed up with DCODE for a special one on one talk with the man himself where you can see him live on the 24th of August. Sign up now at dcode.id/progressivelab to be a part of his mentoring group and get the chance to bring home his artwork!

episode_name: Pod.53 TALKS ABOUT SAILING FROM EAST TO WEST with Rich Brian
description: Talks about exploration, making it and famous friends.   Brian Immanuel or also known as Rich Brian is an Indonesian rapper, singer, songwriter and record producer. He left Indonesia to the States when he was 17 after his viral debut single on Youtube and was signed by 88 Rising, an American mass media company founded by Sean Miyashiro. Brian recently released The Sailor, his second album that spoke a lot about home, family and the roots. We sat with him when he was in town for a quick 20 minutes podcast. Be the first to hear!

episode_name: Pod.52 TALKS ABOUT A CUP OF AUTHENTICITY with Muhammad Aga
description: Talks about rockabilly, competing and a Dad’s promise.   This podcast is the definition of not taking anything for granted. A cup of coffee that wakes everyone up in the morning and get everyone pumped goes through a numerous amount of process that was explained best by Indonesia’s representing barista, Muhammad Aga. Despite the amount of competitions won and held here and around the world, we sat down with Aga about life and what it means to be at the end of the chain. Listen now to hear all about it.

episode_name: Pod.51 TALKS ABOUT THE UNEXPECTED START with Lolita Agustine
description: In this episode, Lolita talked about being scammed, selling cigarettes and living the life.  You may seen Lolita talking about your favorite football team on air or maybe presenting the hottest news on air, but despite all that - Lolita is a soon to be a mother that loves to go out to the unknown (mostly alone). Listen to today’s episode on how she got to where she is through the surprises life gives.

episode_name: Pod.50 TALKS ABOUT LIFE OFF STAGE with Raisa
description: In this episode, Raisa talked about dreams coming true, a comeback and momlife  We kicked off season two with the one and only Raisa Andriana, an Indonesian singer-songwriter who is now above and beyond the industry chart. Despite her many hits and awards, Raisa recently became a mother to a beautiful daughter and took some break off stage. Check out today’s episode to know what her break was like and the plans on coming back.

episode_name: Ep. 25 Monday Family Meeting - The End with Ernanda, Sese, Iyas, Jordy, Farid
description: In this episode of Monday Family Meeting, we say goodbye.

episode_name: Pod.49 TALKS ABOUT REPRESENTING FEELINGS with Sal Priadi
description: In this episode, Sal Priadi talked about adaptation, his worst heartbreak, and making people cry.  Salmantyo Ashirizky Priadi or mostly known as Sal Priadi is the latest soloist to move to the concrete jungle of Jakarta. The born and raised Malang musician have released a few singles on digital platforms including Amin Paling Serius featuring Nadin Amizah and recently collaborated with Hindia (Baskara Putra) produced by the talented Petra Sihombing titled Belum Tidur. In this episode, Sal tells us what it means to live in the big city J and how his songs relate so much to the generation of broken hearts. Stick around to the end of the episode for a little surprise by the man himself.

episode_name: Ep. 24 Monday Family Meeting - Tattoos with Jordy and Tuko
description: In this episode of Monday Family Meeting Jordy and Tuco talked about getting inked for the first time and how it escelated quickly. They also talked about the permanent decision on their bodies and who are responsible it. Hear more on today's episode of Monday Family Meeting.

episode_name: Pod.48 TALKS ABOUT BEING THE GOOD KID IN THE MAD CITY GUNDALA with Joko Anwar
description: In this episode, Joko Anwar talked about being the good kid in a mad city, the process fulfilling dreams and introduces Gundala  Joko Anwar is an International award winning film director, screenwriter and producer. Since a young boy growing up watching horror and kung fu films, Joko’s interest have always been in the film industry and so far he is making it real well. Although most of Joko’s work lately gave most of us goosebumps, he is stepping up the game by introducing us to Gundala, a local superhero that was made by Harya Suraminata in the late 80s. Hear what you can expect from the upcoming superhero and what it takes to be the Joko today.

episode_name: Ep. 23 Monday Family Meeting - Final Project with Iyas, Farid and Jessica
description: In this episode of monday family meeting, Jeli, Farid and Iyas talks about the final stage before graduation known as the final project. Check todays episode out to know how its done!

episode_name: Pod.47 TALKS ABOUT MAKING PEOPLE LAUGH AROUND THE WORLD with Pandji Pragiwaksono
description: In this episode, Pandji talked about being inspired by jason mraz, early life of radio broadcasting and going around the world 3 times. It’s difficult to explain who or what Pandji is, but in the beginning, it was as a radio announcer he began introducing himself to public and then his love towards rap music inspired him to make a few hits and performed at plenty music festivals around Indonesia. In between all that he is also a comedian, actor, television presenter and book writer. Today, he makes people laugh for a living doing stand ups here and there and by that we mean going around the world 3 times. Hear how this all began, what he’s up to and a few conversation about his political choice for the city of Jakarta.

episode_name: Ep. 22 Monday Family Meeting - Futuria with Stephen and Alex
description: In this episode of Monday Family Meeting, Stephen and Alex talked about the upcoming project held in Semarang this coming weekend until the 14th of July called Futuria, a brand activation from Telkomsigma a subsidiary of Telkom indonesia that potrays the future of Indonesia that combines the culture, nature and technology. Hope to see you all in a bit!

episode_name: Pod.46 TALKS ABOUT EMBRACING THE ODD AND BEAUTY WITHIN with Cindercella
description: In this episode, Cindercella talked about her early cheerleading career, being true to the world and meeting super famous people. This is makna talks  Marcella Febrianne Hadikusumo or mostly known as Cindercella is a beauty enthusiast that is known for her oddly beautiful make up style and her out going personality. But above all that, she is a middle child from a Chinese Indonesian family that supports her both in the beauty world and singing career. She is now focusing on making people believe in themselves and accepting their flaws through her social media. Listen to how she became who she is in the game and get your inspired hat on!

episode_name: Ep. 21 Monday Family Meeting - Manis with Samuel and Emma
description: In this episode of Monday Family Meeting, Samuel and Emma talks about the sweet trends of F&B. They shared experiences on drinking their childhood treats, new unique flavors on the market, to the most bizarre bubble drink incident in China.  Take a sip of your favorite boba tea and enjoy today's episode!

episode_name: Pod.45 TALKS ABOUT PLANTS ON AIR with Patsy
description: In this episode, Patsy talked about being the pioneer of selling plants online, getting down and dirty and putting community first Patricia or best known as Patsy is the founder of Shop with Sky, an online plant selling store that sells any kind of living plants for any needs. 3 years ago she started building the company not knowing what to expect. This is a story of how compassion and hard work can pay the bills.

episode_name: Ep. 20 Monday Family Meeting - The Intern with Rachel and Karina
description: In this episode of Monday Family Meeting, Rachel and Karina talks about how they spend the Eid al-Fitr holiday with their families. They both share what it feels like to be the interns at Makna, and what's next for their future career. Check out today's episode and have a great week back at the office!

episode_name: Ep.44 TALKS ABOUT BEING POWERFUL, FAITHFUL AND BEAUTIFUL with Sivia Azizah
description: With over 1million followers on Instagram, Sivia Azizah is known for many of her talents - a few of them are singing, acting, broadcasting, sneaker shopping and everything in between. Despite all that, Sivia this past year have been an icon for the muslim youth as she represents her true self with the hijab and giving a pinch of streetwear. MaknaTalks teamed up with Clear Indonesia to talk with Sivia as their Brand Ambassador and at the same time to close the month of Ramadan with style.

episode_name: Pod.43 TALKS ABOUT LOVING IT ENOUGH TO MAKE IT with Anugrah Aditya
description: Anugrah Aditya is also known as Adityalogy, a sneaker and pop culture enthusiast that is well known in the streetwear industry. But before there was Adityalogy, he was known by his hit single “Be Mine” which blew up in the year 2012 and made him question his passion in the industry of music. Listen to today’s episode to check out what are the most sentimental kicks for him, meeting Virgil Abloh up close and his comeback to music!

episode_name: Ep. 19 Monday Family Meeting - Mudik with Jordy and Nadira
description: In this episode of Monday Family Meeting, Nadira talks about what it feels like to come back home in the end of this holy month of Ramadan and Jordy talks about what it feels like to spend the day at home. They both share about the feeling of togetherness at home even with different beliefs and culture. Check out today's episode to hear all about it. Also, for you who are hitting the road soon. Stay safe and say hello to the family!

episode_name: Pod.42 TALKS ABOUT DEALING BY LISTENING with Baskara Putra
description: Baskara Putra is known by a lot of names in the music and creative industry. Some may know him as Hindia for his solo career, some by Wordfangs from his socials and some know him as Baskara the lead vocals of Feast, a band he started with when he was in University of Indonesia. After releasing a few singles as Hindia and 2 albums from Feast, Baskara is nowhere from stopping. He is preparing for more to come. Listen here to figure out all about it!

description: In this episode, Bam talked about being the start, Kevin talked about his way up and Bayu talked about knowing whats right and they  talked about being the greatest ever.

episode_name: Pod. 27 TALKS ABOUT THE SURPRISES OF LIFE with Putri Marino
description: In this episode: Putri talks about the island of the gods, career change and her first Christmas with her small family. - Putri Marino is a new mother of a beautiful daughter, Surinala. She began her acting career as an Adventurous host 3 years ago and everything went upwards from there; from winning Piala Citra, Festival Film Tempo to i-Cinema Awards in 2017. Born and raised to Balinese and Italian parents, Putri now stays in Jakarta after numerous travels between the two countries to seek her passion. Her journey to success was based on her guts and willing to do the unexpected. Now married and settling to this concrete jungle, Putri is starting a new chapter with her small family of three, starting by spending her first Christmas with them. listen to it here. - Follow us on Twitter: @maknatalks Instagram: maknatalks

episode_name: Pod. 26 TALKS ABOUT IF YOU WANT IT, YOU DO IT with Dimas Danang
description: In this episode: Danang talks about being Tony Stark, thoughts on being called a dynamic duo and keeping it quiet. - Dimas Danang is a TV host and ex radio presenter that you have probably heard on your rush hour traffic. He is also a vocalist and guitarist of "Why Phoebe". Jakarta Post called him and his partner (Darto) the dynamic duo of the year in 2015. Despite being known for that, Dimas wants to contribute to this era of digital as a solo personality with his on going company called "Sami-sami". In here you can listen about his journey from a broken home, being critical in education and what it takes to make it out there. - Follow us on Twitter: @maknatalks Instagram: maknatalks

episode_name: Pod 25. TALKS ABOUT GROWING UP ABROAD, PLAYING CHARACTERS AND TYING THE KNOT with Ario Bayu
description: In this episode Ario talks about moving, the beginning of acting and marriage. - Ario Bayu, born in Jakarta to Javanese parents spent most of his early days in the land of the sheeps, New Zealand. He is an Indonesian actor best known for his roles as Soekarno, Kala as Eros, Dead Mine as Captain Tino, and in the Hollywood production Java Heat as Lieutenant Hashim He returned to Indonesia in 2004 with the intent to pursue his acting and music ambitions with his experience in Hamilton, New Zealand and studies at the globe theatre, London but the sad truth: no one really cared about his achievements during that period. Listen to this podcast as he speaks the truth about the industry, the power of fame and how he found love in Jogjakarta that brought him to tying the knot in France. - Follow us on Twitter: @maknatalks Instagram: maknatalks

episode_name: Pod 24. TALKS ABOUT GROWING UP STRICT AND FALLING IN LOVE WITH DIFFERENCES with Ellyse Sinsilia
description: In this episode Sese talks in mandarin, her journey struggles of love and building a beautiful family - Ellyse Sinsilia or well known as Sese in and out of the Makna HQ, is a mother of a beautiful boy, Saka. Her career in the world of digital advertising was a huge part of her life until a decision of building a family comes to mind. Despite growing up in a stereotypical asian culture she fell in love with someone on the other side of her box, Ernanda Putra. Listen to her journey of love here. - Follow us on Twitter: @maknatalks Instagram: maknatalks

episode_name: Pod 23. TALKS ABOUT THE DARK SIDE OF MUSIC AND GROWING UP IN A WAR with Teddy Adhitya
description: In this episode Teddy talks about his dark childhood, not being accepted and his fashion icon. - After releasing his debut Album "NOTHING IS REAL" in early 2017 , he is ending this year with a single of his second Album which is due to release next year (2018). "WHY WOULD I BE" is available on all digital platforms. Teddy Adhitya, A 27 year old Ambonese born in Yogyakarta is today known as a singer and songwriter - but before fame from the music industry kicked in, back in the day he was a star on the tennis field taking 5 national titles home. Hear what Teddy have to say about his passion in music and growing up in fear. - Follow us on Twitter: @maknatalks Instagram: maknatalks

episode_name: Pod 22. TALKS ABOUT KEEPING IT MANUAL AND THE IMPORTANCE OF LAUGHTER with Hadi Ismanto
description: In this episode Hadi Ismanto talks about home, humour and teamwork. - Hadi Ismanto, founder of Manual Jakarta, an independent online publication focusing on lifestyle and culture in Jakarta, MALT, a Jakarta-based graphic design agency and other companies he's made along the years. Born and raised outside of Jakarta, he fell in love with the culture and inspired by studying up abroad. Currently, promoting his third issue of the Manual Jakarta magazine that runs around the topic of Humor. - Follow us on Twitter: @maknatalks Instagram: maknatalks
